"German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mildenhall","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: locative name from Mildenhall (Wilts).","2  English: locative name from Mildenhall (Suffolk)."],"variants":[{"name":"Mildinhall","meanings":["English:  see  Mildenhall  ."]},{"name":"Mindenhall","meanings":["English: variant of   Mildenhall   (1)."]},{"name":"Minall","meanings":["English: a local pronunciation of   Mildenhall   (1), from the Wilts place-name, which is recorded as  <i>Mildenhall otherwise Minal</i> in 1760."]}]},{"name":"Andrew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":15,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":24,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":59,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Andrew de Mildenhall was born in 1200, in England as the son of Sir John de Mildenhall and Jane. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1200–":"1200–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1130":"1130","england":"England"},"fi":{"1200–":"1200–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1130":"1130","england":"England"},"fr":{"1200–":"1200–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1130":"1130","england":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Andrew de Mildenhall est né en 1200, à Angleterre, fils de Sir John de Mildenhall et Jane. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1200–":"1200–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1259":"1259","1215":"12